  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help PASITOS continue to serve our community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PASITOS has been providing services to children and young adults with autism in Tijuana for 21 years. Though our campus is closed due to COVID-19, we are required by Mexican law to continue paying the salaries of our teachers, psychologists, and support staff. We have begun offering deeply discounted remote therapy sessions and free remote parental training/support. While closed, our monthly operating costs are approximately $15,000. We have only one more month of operating reserves on hand.</narrative>
  </description>
